Package com.geom.model

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ConvexQuadrilateral
    Implements convex quadrilateral shapes models: any line drawn through the polygon (and not tangent to an edge or corner) meets its boundary exactly twice.
    EmptyFigure
    Implements an empty shape model.
    EquilateralTriangle
    Implements equilateral triangles All the sides that have the same lengths and all the angles are equal in measure i.e 60°.
    Factory
    Class that implements the creation of a geometric shape Handles aligned points and points that have the same coordinates
    FactoryPolygonal
    Handles the creation of polygonal shapes.
    FactoryQuadrilateral
    Handles the creation of quadrilateral shapes.
    FactoryTriangular
    This class handles the creation of triangular shapes
    Figure
    This class implements the most basic shapes, without any condition regarding number of points, lengths.
    IsoscelesTriangle
    Implements Isosceles triangle An isosceles triangle has two sides of equal length
    Line
    Implements a geometric shape formed by two points This is usually called line if it is at least semi-bounded, or segment if else.
    Parallelogram
    In Euclidean geometry, a parallelogram is a (non self-intersecting) quadrilateral with two pairs of parallel sides.
    Polygon
    Implements a polygon shape In elementary geometry, a polygon is a plane figure that is bounded by a finite chain of straight line segments closing in a loop to form a closed chain or circuit.
    Punct
    Implements a 'Figure' forms by one point
    Quadrilateral
    Implements quadrilateral shapes
    Rectangle
    Implements rectangular shapes A rectangle is any quadrilateral with four right angles.
    RegularPolygon
    Implements regular polygons i.e equilateral shapes
    Rhombus
    Implements a particular quadrilateral shape model: A rhombus In Euclidean geometry, a rhombus(◊), plural rhombi or rhombuses, is a simple (non-self-intersecting) quadrilateral whose four sides all have the same length.
    RightIsoscelesTriangle
    Implements right isosceles triangles It is a right triangle with the two legs (and their corresponding angles) equal.
    RightTriangle
    Implements right triangle.
    Square
    Class implements the Square shape model.
    Trapezoid
    Implements trapezoid.
    Triangle
    Implements triangular shapes A tringle is a 3-sided polygon sometimes (but not very commonly).
